Secondly, The Subjects of this priviledge are described: as many as received him. This Text describes them by that 2. very grace, Faith, which gives them their title and right to Christ and his benefits; and by that very act of faith which primarily conferrs their right to his person, and secondarily to his benefits, viz. receiving him: there be many graces besides faith, but faith only is the grace that gives us right to Christ: and there be many acts of faith besides receiving, but this receiving or embracing of Christ is the justifying and saving act: as many as received him, 
